genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica nortena chilena
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Musica Nortena Chilena is a style of music that originated in the northern regions of Chile. It is characterized by the use of accordion, guitar, and percussion instruments. The music is often played at festivals and celebrations and is known for its energetic rhythms and catchy melodies.
